			<Description>Thermopolium</Description>
			<Civilopedia>In the ancient Greco-Roman world, a thermopolium was a commercial establishment where it was possible to purchase ready-to-eat food. The forerunner of today's restaurant, the items served at the thermopolia are sometimes compared to modern fast food. These places were mainly used by the poor or those who simply could not afford a private kitchen, sometimes leading them to be scorned by the upper class.</Civilopedia>
			<Strategy>The Thermopolium can only be constructed in a city with improved salt, spices, sugar, truffles, citrus or olives resources nearby. The Thermopolium increases the [ICON_GOLD] Gold output of each such resource the city has access to.</Strategy>
			<Help>Each source of [ICON_RES_SALT] Salt, [ICON_RES_SPICES] Spices, [ICON_RES_SUGAR] Sugar, [ICON_RES_TRUFFLES] Truffles, [ICON_RES_CITRUS] Citrus and [ICON_RES_OLIVE] Olives worked by this City produces +1 [ICON_GOLD] Gold.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]City must have at least one of these resources worked nearby.</Help>
